You can change the color of a <span> on mouse over using JavaScript. Here's an example of how to do it:

First, create a <span> element with a class of "mouseover":

<span class="mouseover">Hover over me!</span>

Then, add an event listener to the <span> element that listens for the "mouseover" event. When the event is triggered, change the color of the <span> element to red:

<span class="mouseover">Hover over me!</span>

<script>
  var span = document.querySelector('.mouseover');
  span.addEventListener('mouseover', function() {
    span.style.color = 'red';
  });
</script>You can also add a "mouseout" event listener to change the color back to the default when the mouse leaves the <span> element:

<span class="mouseover">Hover over me!</span>

<script>
  var span = document.querySelector('.mouseover');
  span.addEventListener('mouseover', function() {
    span.style.color = 'red';
  });
  span.addEventListener('mouseout', function() {
    span.style.color = 'black';
  });
</script

In LaTeX, you can create a footnote for the authors list by using the \footnote command. The authors list should be placed in the \bibliographystyle{unsrt} environment, and the \footnote command should be placed after the last author's name.

Here is an example:

\begin{thebibliography}{99}
\bibitem{Smith1999}
Smith, J. (1999). Title of paper. \emph{Journal Name}, \textbf{10}(2), 123-134.
\bibitem{Doe2000}
Doe, J. (2000). Another title. \emph{Journal Name}, \textbf{11}(3), 456-467.
\bibitem{AuthorList2001}
Author List, A. (2001). Yet another title. \emph{Journal Name}, \textbf{12}(4), 789-800.
\footnotetext{The authors are listed in order of their contribution to the paper.}
\end{thebibliography}

In this example, the footnote is created using the \footnotetext command. The text of the footnote is "The authors are listed in order of their contribution to the paper."
